Pizza Snack (located in Hammond, Indiana) is a below decent foodie place. I have bought food from there about 3 times now and I can say that you have to a certain taste to enjoy their food. I sampled the pizza, it was okay but I have had better pizza options at other places throughout Chicago and the state of Indiana. Chicken wings were on the dry side and the fries weren't that tasty either. They should change their food vendor next time. Otherwise, the food that I ordered didn't hurt my bank account or wallet either.

Finally found a place that has great pizza, but terrible service.  The employees running the front desk have no idea how to run a business.  Everytime I call for a pizza, I'm told different things, from you can't add that topping to this is the way we do things.  The employees at the front desk have such an attitude that before I even order, I made to feel like an inconvience.  The pizza slices they sell are sometimes held overnight to sell the next day.  Another time, I ordered a beef and watched them microwave it in front of me and was told we always do it this way.  I'm very disappointed to write this kind of review.
